        <p><hi rend="bold">Georg Siemens (1839&#x2013;1901),</hi> German banker and politician, founding director of the Deutsche Bank and its first chairman until 1900.  A focal point of his work was the financing of the international railway system, amongst others in the Ottoman Empire (the Baghdad railway) and in the USA (the Northern Pacific railway).</p>
        <p><hi rend="italic">Contributor:</hi>  Marko Deisinger</p>
